beer_description:
Our famous and always asked for Czech-style hoppy Pilsner. Dry-hopped with Mandarina and lagered for over five weeks. Wheat free

The 4th Lager to be brewed at Iron Springs, this Czech Pilsner is crisp, light,& super refreshing and a perfect beer to go with these hot Marin days (and nights).
Smooth, malty, and complex.  This sessionable red is a delicious Trout River classic.
This beer will wake up your senses to fine American hops! Batch 69 exhibits a nice bite and finishes off with pleasant notes of citrus and pine.
A fruity, high gravity trippel
A fruity golden ale with flavours of tropical resinous fruits abundant in the mouth, and a sensuous citrus finish.
Aroma is caramel, fruity, hoppy, with citrus and grassy notes. Juicy-spicy character, earthy and a bit spicy. Alcohol helps to dry out the finish.
2010 GABF Pro-Am regional  winner
The dark amber colour and body derived from crystal malt combined with the Goldings aroma hops gives the beer just the right warmth and flavour - explicitly Santa's choice.
As the New Year begins launch yourself into this pale ruby coloured beer. Well balanced and rounded this beer is perfect for getting you to your destination fast.

beer_name: Paulaner Hefe-Weizen / Hefe-Wei?bier Naturtr?b / Natural Wheat

beer_description:
Convict Hill Stout pours a deep obsidian color with a thick, creamy head. Flaked oats create a rich, creamy body that tempers the bitter roasted barley flavors of this robust, heady ale. The name Convict Hill Stout was inspired by Convict Hill in southwest Austin, where limestone was quarried for the Texas capitol building.

Malt: 2 Row, Roasted Barley, Chocolate, Flaked Oats.

Hops: Nugget 

Yeast: American Ale (Chico)
An American Dark I.P.A. brewed with over 11 pounds of Simcoe hops, and finished with a dry hop addition of Simcoe and Amarillo.
Harking back to the 1880's (sic) with a Traditional Thames Valley brown Porter. Roasted malt and coffee on the nose, smooth malt with liquorice and chocolate on the palate.
A Strong Pale Ale
Cask!!
This is Cigar City?s Bolita Brown Ale aged for 5 months in a Maker?s Mark Bourbon Barrel. Only about 170 bottles released to the public. Hand numbered.
beer_name: Bourbon Barrel-Aged Bolita Double Brown Ale

beer_description: The Abominable SnowBeer is dangerously delicious. Our winter seasonal is a tasty belgian double with with a nice character of citrus, banana, and a little spice on the finish. Perfect for when you have successfully outrun the infamous winter beast.

It?s the Return of the King! Our Royal Imperial IPA summons an intense hop presence of lemongrass, mango, and papaya. Follow the royal procession from every citrusy sniff to each bitter sip, and notice the vibrant hop character shining brilliantly throughout! So regal, so royal, so NOBLE.

A Silver Medal winner in Strong Ales at the 1996 Great American Beer Festival. This Irish-style strong ale is brewed with a secret blend of five imported specialty malts. Not too hoppy in order to emphasize the complex malt flavor and fruity aroma.
Pisgah Pale is a perfect blend of rich organic malts with whole-leaf Chinook and Nugget hops.  A crisp, clean profile makes this, our flagship beer, distinct.
Refreshment at its finest.  This easy drinking lager will make your day. Not too heavy, not too hoppy. Crisp and clean with a light golden color. Saaz hops help provide that true lager taste.

Roasty, chocolate tones swirled with oatmeal smoothness and dark as the night. The Dark Star crashes, pouring its light into ashes, so follow as the Lady of Velvet recedes in the nights of goodbye. This one is too smooth ? and at 8.0% ABV, dangerous.

beer_description:
A massive American style Imperial IPA hopped and dry hopped with 3
pounds per barrel Citra. Huge aromas and flavors of citrus and mango.

A massive American style Imperial IPA hopped and dry hopped with 3
pounds per barrel Citra. Huge aromas and flavors of citrus and mango.

Fish Tale Organic India Pale Ale is a medium-bodied beer with a rich golden color. The organic pale and crystal malts lay down a firm malt body. This provides the backbone for an assertive hop profile featuring organic Pacific Gem. The moment the Mighty Fish Brewers sampled this pungent and resinous New Zealand hop, they knew it would be perfect for their Organic I.P.A. The result: A Cascadian treasure.
beer_name: Fish Tale Organic India Pale Ale (IPA)

beer_description: This Dark Ale is brewed using 6 malts including Dark Chocolate Malt, Dark Carmel, Roasted Barley and a touch of Cherry-wood Smoked Malt. It is very well balanced; the hops and a light smokiness come through in the finish. This is our version of a recipe developed by the fine team at New Abanian Brewing Co. in New Albany, IN and has historical roots in Indiana brewing.

The star performers at all county fairs, audacious wing walkers take to the sky performing high-flying acrobatics and daredevil feats to capture the imagination of onlookers with stunts not to be attempted at home. Enjoy the show as WingWalker quenches an appetite for entertainment in thrill seekers near and far.

The original Sehr Crisp from Sixpoint. Brewed with noble hops for indelible sehr crisp flavor.

Made in cooperation with Jeppe from Olbuttikken in Copenhagen. Jeppe provides the blueberries for the beer, and it is brewed at Cantillon and then shipped back to Copenhagen and only sold at Olbutikken.

beer_description: Vern is our take on the classic Pacific Northwest IPA. Lots of hop and a lighter body make this city boy shine.
All grain kit from Northern Brewer. Modeled after The Landlord from Timothy Taylor.

Smooth and bready sweet up front, with
a clean, dry-herbal hop finish. Brewed exclusively for The Watering Hole.

Avoid the scrum & make sure you score an early try as our most popular seasonal ale makes a winning return.

A full-bodied malty beer with a clean citrus aroma tackles your taste buds & kicks its opponents into touch. Available Feb/March.

Standing 12 ft. tall at the center of the brew deck is our HopBack vessel; here, whole flower hops swirl in hot wort coaxing hop oil into aromas of grapefruit pith and pinesap. This bright hop nose is counterbalanced with malt tones of toffee and caramel.

Surly Mild is a session ale brewed with pale ale, caramel and chocolate malts. Light brown in color with malt forward flavors of sweet toasted bread and cocoa are balanced by a crisp hop finish. A post holiday session ale? What?s a session ale you ask? It is a low alcohol beer packed with color and flavor, designed for a ?session? of multiple servings
A traditional German-style pale maibock that was lagered (aged) over 6 weeks.

Our Quadrupel is a mahogany-colored ale with a rich sweetness, light spiciness and high alcohol content. The use of several different malted barleys and wheat creates a caramel character, while a Belgian abbey yeast strain produces raisin, plum and figs flavors. European hops provide balance to the mix.
Aged in wine barrels.
A Russian Style Imperial Stout named after the late night TV host of ?Lenny?s Inferno? than ran in the ?70?s and early ?80?s. Deceptively smooth.

The St.Bernardus Abt 12 is the pride of our stable, the nec plus ultra of our brewery. Abbey ale brewed in the classic 'Quadrupel' style of Belgium's best Abbey Ales. Dark with a full, ivory-colored head. It has a fruity aroma, full of complex flavours and excells because of its long bittersweet finish with a hoppy bite. (10,0% ABV) Worldwide seen as one of the best beers in the world. It's a very balanced beer, with a full-bodied taste and a perfect equilibrium between malty, bitter and sweet. One of the original recipes from the days of license-brewing for the Trappist monks of Westvleteren
Golden elixir! Light & complex with a yeasty nose, fruity esters and malty dryness.
A high hopped, high alcohol, high bitterness, true IPA that is like an invigorating open handed slap of citrus awesomeness!
A medium bodied ale with a malty caramel flavor. Very smooth and flavorful. Our most popular beer.
